1
00:00:03,253 --> 00:00:05,756
[theme music plays]

2
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:28,380
ALLY

3
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,061
[console beeps]

4
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:49,109
[retina scanner beeps]

5
00:02:03,248 --> 00:02:05,042
-[buzzer]
-Hmm?

6
00:02:06,335 --> 00:02:09,129
[Aizawa] Oh, okay! Maybe the belt…

7
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:13,425
[buzzer]

8
00:02:14,176 --> 00:02:15,761
[Aizawa] Huh? What now?

9
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:21,224
Well, looks like this system
is gonna take some getting used to.

10
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:23,143
[Aizawa] Fine!

11
00:02:24,311 --> 00:02:25,646
How's this? Huh?

12
00:02:26,229 --> 00:02:27,648
[door opens]

13
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:28,982
Good morning!

14
00:02:29,399 --> 00:02:30,442
[Matsuda] Huh?

15
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:34,696
What's wrong? Did you get hurt?

16
00:02:34,780 --> 00:02:36,490
Oh, this? Kind of.

17
00:02:37,074 --> 00:02:39,868
Uh… I had a little fight
with my wife, and…

18
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,912
It's just that my daughter
is still young,

19
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:44,289
and I'm hardly ever at home
as it is, so…

20
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:47,959
Oh, yes. It's probably best
if you sleep at home.

21
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:50,045
Well, you're gonna be missing out.

22
00:02:50,253 --> 00:02:52,214
The rooms in this place are amazing.

23
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:54,883
If I were you, I'd just move
the whole family in here.

24
00:02:55,008 --> 00:02:58,220
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
that's easy for you to say as a bachelor.

25
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:01,056
-Where are they?
-[Matsuda] Oh, they're on a date.

26
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:03,392
Last we checked all of them
were up in Misa-Misa's room.

27
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:04,935
[Yagami] Hmm.

28
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:07,270
[Aizawa] Surveillance cameras, huh?

29
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:10,607
Well, since we know Misa has
some connection to the Second Kira,

30
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:12,359
I guess it does make sense.

31
00:03:12,484 --> 00:03:16,154
But for God's sake, Matsuda,
would you stop with this Misa-Misa crap?

32
00:03:16,279 --> 00:03:17,614
[Matsuda] Oh… yeah. Sure.

33
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:19,282
Man!

34
00:03:19,366 --> 00:03:22,285
This is gotta be
the lamest date I've ever been on.

35
00:03:22,536 --> 00:03:24,746
No, no, no, please. Just pretend
I'm not even here, okay?

36
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:27,624
By the way, are you gonna
eat that piece of cake?

37
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,127
[Misa] Cake makes you fat.
I'm not gonna eat any.

38
00:03:30,419 --> 00:03:32,421
Actually, I've found that you
don't gain any weight

39
00:03:32,546 --> 00:03:34,548
as long as you burn calories
by using your brain.

40
00:03:34,715 --> 00:03:36,967
[Misa] Hm! So now
you're calling me stupid?

41
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,927
Fine then. I'll give you the piece of cake

42
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:41,012
as long as you agree
to leave me and Light alone.

43
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:42,806
Even if I leave you two alone,

44
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:44,933
I'm still gonna be watching
on surveillance cameras.

45
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:47,519
-So, it wouldn't make any difference.
-You pervert!

46
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:49,688
Could you stop
with your creepy hobby?

47
00:03:49,813 --> 00:03:52,482
You can call me whatever you like.
Last chance for cake.

48
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:54,317
Okay, then.

49
00:03:54,443 --> 00:03:56,486
I'll just close the curtains
and turn off the lights.

50
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:58,989
[Ryuzaki] We have infrared cameras
in here as well.

51
00:03:59,072 --> 00:04:01,199
-[Misa groans]
-What's wrong with you?

52
00:04:01,324 --> 00:04:03,994
I thought moving here
was supposed to help us catch Kira,

53
00:04:04,202 --> 00:04:07,164
but since we've been here
you don't seem all that motivated to me.

54
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,750
[Ryuzaki] Not motivated?

55
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:12,002
You're right.

56
00:04:12,461 --> 00:04:14,004
Actually, I'm depressed.

57
00:04:14,421 --> 00:04:15,714
Depressed? What for?

58
00:04:16,173 --> 00:04:17,591
Well, hmm…

59
00:04:18,467 --> 00:04:20,761
Truthfully, all this time,
I thought that you were Kira

60
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:23,388
and my entire case
hinged on that fact. [gulps]

61
00:04:23,555 --> 00:04:27,225
I guess I just can't get past the fact
that my deduction was wrong.

62
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:31,062
Although, having said that,
I'm still suspicious of you.

63
00:04:31,521 --> 00:04:33,064
That's why we're wearing these.

64
00:04:33,565 --> 00:04:37,194
And we also know
Kira can control people's actions.

65
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,196
Which means it's highly likely

66
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:42,824
that Kira was controlling your actions
so that I would suspect you.

67
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:46,703
If I assume both you and Misa
were being controlled by him,

68
00:04:47,621 --> 00:04:51,291
then everything we've observed so far
makes a lot more sense to me.

69
00:04:52,334 --> 00:04:55,170
If that's what you think,
Misa and I were both Kira

70
00:04:55,337 --> 00:04:57,672
during the time
we were being controlled, right?

71
00:04:57,923 --> 00:04:58,840
[Ryuzaki] Yes,

72
00:04:58,965 --> 00:05:00,967
I don't think I could’ve been
wrong about that.

73
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:03,011
The two of you are Kira.

74
00:05:03,595 --> 00:05:04,888
[both] Hmm.

75
00:05:06,765 --> 00:05:08,433
[Ryuzaki] If what I'm thinking is correct,

76
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:11,186
when your confinement began
you were Kira.

77
00:05:11,353 --> 00:05:14,064
I don't believe it's coincidence
that as soon as you were in prison

78
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:15,607
all the killing stopped.

79
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:19,069
Until then, everything
pointed to you being Kira,

80
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:22,489
but after two weeks,
criminals actually began dying again.

81
00:05:22,697 --> 00:05:23,865
KIRA RETURNS

82
00:05:25,534 --> 00:05:28,495
Based on that evidence,
I can only conclude that…

83
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:31,873
Kira's power passes between people.

84
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:35,836
That's an interesting idea.
But if it's true,

85
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:38,630
it'll be nearly impossible for us
to catch Kira.

86
00:05:38,797 --> 00:05:41,258
Yes. That's why I'm overwhelmed.

87
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,094
Even if we catch someone
under his control,

88
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:47,180
they'll likely lose their powers
and any memory of their crimes.

89
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:50,433
So, in the end,
pursuing them becomes futile.

90
00:05:50,851 --> 00:05:53,645
But at this point we have no way
of knowing if that's the case.

91
00:05:53,770 --> 00:05:54,938
Cheer up, would ya?

92
00:05:55,689 --> 00:05:56,606
"Cheer up"?

93
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:58,233
No, I'm sorry, I can't.

94
00:05:58,567 --> 00:06:01,570
It's probably better
if I just stop trying so hard.

95
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:04,656
By chasing Kira so desperately

96
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:06,783
we're just putting our lives at risk
for nothing.

97
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:07,868
Yes.

98
00:06:08,159 --> 00:06:09,661
It's just a waste of time.

99
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:11,913
[sighs]

100
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,164
Ryuzaki…

101
00:06:13,415 --> 00:06:14,374
Huh?

102
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:16,668
-[Ryuzaki grunts]
-[Misa screams]

103
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:19,963
-[Ryuzaki and Light grunting]
-[objects clatter]

104
00:06:21,006 --> 00:06:23,008
[yelps]

105
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:26,094
[groans]

106
00:06:26,177 --> 00:06:28,513
-[Misa moans]
-[Ryuzaki groans]

107
00:06:29,014 --> 00:06:30,473
You know, that really hurt.

108
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:33,852
That's enough.
You don't feel like doing anything,

109
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,980
just because your genius deduction
was wrong and I'm not Kira?

110
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:40,817
[Ryuzaki grunts] Fine.
Perhaps I phrased it the wrong way.

111
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:43,278
I meant it would be pointless for us
to make a move,

112
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:44,738
so we shouldn't even bother.

113
00:06:44,821 --> 00:06:46,656
If we don't chase Kira,
he will never be caught.

114
00:06:46,781 --> 00:06:49,034
Is that what you want?
If you were just gonna give up,

115
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:51,077
then why did you involve
all those innocent people?

116
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:55,206
More importantly, what was the point
of putting Misa and me behind bars?

117
00:06:55,582 --> 00:06:56,791
I understand.

118
00:06:57,959 --> 00:07:00,795
But still, whatever the reason…

119
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,131
-[Ryuzaki grunts]
-[Misa screams]

120
00:07:04,716 --> 00:07:06,509
…an eye for an eye, my friend.

121
00:07:09,054 --> 00:07:11,973
[both scream]

122
00:07:15,268 --> 00:07:17,938
-[Ryuzaki and Light grunting]
-Ooh!

123
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:22,943
[Ryuzaki grunts]
It's not my deduction that was wrong.

124
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:24,903
The fact is, I can say

125
00:07:25,028 --> 00:07:28,782
that Light Yagami is Kira and
Misa Amane is the Second Kira,

126
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:31,326
but it won't be enough
to solve the case.

127
00:07:31,409 --> 00:07:33,495
And that's why I'm a little depressed.

128
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:35,830
-Is that so unreasonable?
-Yes.

129
00:07:36,164 --> 00:07:38,416
Yes, it is.
Besides, you should hear yourself.

130
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:41,252
It's as if you won't be satisfied
unless I'm Kira.

131
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:44,798
I… I won't be satisfied
unless you're Kira?

132
00:07:45,632 --> 00:07:47,717
Well, there may be some truth to that.

133
00:07:48,927 --> 00:07:51,888
In fact, now that you mention it,
you're right.

134
00:07:52,514 --> 00:07:54,265
I think I wanted you to be Kira.

135
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:57,060
[grunts]

136
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:00,981
As I said before, an eye for an eye.

137
00:08:02,107 --> 00:08:04,693
I'm a lot stronger than I look, you know.

138
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,445
[Ryuzaki grunts]

139
00:08:07,654 --> 00:08:09,948
We've got to call the room and stop them!

140
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:11,950
-[phone ringing]
-[both] Huh?

141
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:14,619
-Yes?
-[Matsuda] Ryuzaki, I've got good news.

142
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:16,496
Misa-Misa is number one

143
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:19,040
in Eighteen Magazine's reader
popularity poll!

144
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:21,001
[Ryuzaki] Oh, I see.

145
00:08:21,251 --> 00:08:22,252
[Matsuda] And get this!

146
00:08:22,335 --> 00:08:24,713
She's gonna get a lead role
in Nishinaka's next movie!

147
00:08:26,089 --> 00:08:27,257
What was that?

148
00:08:27,549 --> 00:08:29,551
Matsuda's acting stupid again.

149
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:30,760
[line beeping]

150
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,429
[Light] Well, that is his specialty.

151
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:35,432
I can hear you, you know.

152
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:40,562
TWO MONTHS LATER

153
00:08:44,274 --> 00:08:45,400
Ryuzaki.

154
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:48,319
I know you're not feeling up to it,
but come over here for a second.

155
00:08:49,112 --> 00:08:50,613
Take a close look at this.

156
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:53,033
-It can't be coincidence.
-Huh?

157
00:08:53,575 --> 00:08:56,077
[Light] All of them were prominent
Japanese businessmen.

158
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:59,205
CEOs whose companies are leaders
in their respective industries.

159
00:08:59,330 --> 00:09:02,292
In just over a month
they all died of heart attacks.

160
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,045
As expected, there's been
a general downturn in the market.

161
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:07,088
With the exception of Yotsuba.

162
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:08,256
In other words,

163
00:09:08,339 --> 00:09:10,759
their deaths have worked
in Yotsuba's favor.

164
00:09:11,259 --> 00:09:12,385
Looking back,

165
00:09:12,469 --> 00:09:15,430
there have been 13 similar deaths
in the past three months.

166
00:09:16,264 --> 00:09:17,265
Your thoughts?

167
00:09:17,474 --> 00:09:21,102
Based on this I can only conclude
that Kira is supporting Yotsuba.

168
00:09:21,561 --> 00:09:24,230
Hm. It could be.
But if what you're saying is true,

169
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:27,859
we can assume that punishing criminals
is not this Kira's real intent.

170
00:09:28,151 --> 00:09:29,069
[Light] Right

171
00:09:29,194 --> 00:09:31,529
Punishing criminals
is a diversion for him.

172
00:09:31,654 --> 00:09:32,781
It obscures the fact

173
00:09:32,906 --> 00:09:36,034
that he is actually killing people
for the benefit of his company.

174
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:37,494
Hmm.

175
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:40,413
Are you…
feeling a bit more motivated now?

176
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:02,268
[man 1] It's funny.
This is starting to feel too easy.

177
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:05,105
Look at all we've done
and no one suspects a thing.

178
00:10:05,188 --> 00:10:08,399
[man 2] Our stock continues to increase
but we've kept it below the radar.

179
00:10:08,483 --> 00:10:09,567
[man 1] Indeed.

180
00:10:09,901 --> 00:10:12,612
Everything appears to be proceeding
according to plan.

181
00:10:14,072 --> 00:10:17,492
That's true. However, there is one thing
that has me concerned.

182
00:10:18,076 --> 00:10:20,203
Those three we had killed last week.

183
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:22,372
Why did all of them die of heart attacks?

184
00:10:22,580 --> 00:10:24,874
I thought we agreed
one would be accidental.

185
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:27,252
You're quite right. We did.

186
00:10:27,335 --> 00:10:30,338
The problem was that we named
a specific location in Japan.

187
00:10:30,797 --> 00:10:33,258
You see, he wasn't even here when he died.

188
00:10:33,424 --> 00:10:35,927
I hear he and his mistress
were in Italy at the time.

189
00:10:36,094 --> 00:10:37,095
Makes sense.

190
00:10:37,178 --> 00:10:40,181
If our request
is physically impossible then…

191
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:44,060
Kira will kill that person
using his default method. A heart attack.

192
00:10:44,185 --> 00:10:46,271
It's just like I was saying last week.

193
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:49,941
If you want it to look believable,
request accidental death or disease

194
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:52,569
and Kira will always find
the quickest way to make it happen.

195
00:10:52,902 --> 00:10:55,864
Anyway, given Kira's history,

196
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:58,867
the police are probably
still focused on the dying criminals.

197
00:10:59,117 --> 00:11:00,618
Quite frankly, if someone was able

198
00:11:00,702 --> 00:11:03,454
to trace the deaths of these people
back to us,

199
00:11:03,705 --> 00:11:05,748
then he would have to be a god.

200
00:11:05,874 --> 00:11:08,293
Besides, we've taken precautions.

201
00:11:09,919 --> 00:11:10,962
-Hm?
-Oh?

202
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:14,174
Hey, Chief! Oh, you too, Mogi!
I've got some great news.

203
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:15,675
This is amazing!

204
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:17,468
I'm not even sure how he figured it out,

205
00:11:17,552 --> 00:11:18,928
but Light has a theory that Kira

206
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,805
is somehow involved
with the Yotsuba Group.

207
00:11:20,972 --> 00:11:21,890
Can you believe it?

208
00:11:22,223 --> 00:11:23,224
Yotsuba?

209
00:11:23,725 --> 00:11:25,143
Uh… yes.

210
00:11:25,935 --> 00:11:27,228
That's probably it.

211
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:28,730
-Good work.
-Huh?

212
00:11:29,689 --> 00:11:31,316
We just spoke with the director

213
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:34,485
and it seems Kira has offered bribes
to a number of politicians.

214
00:11:34,944 --> 00:11:37,989
[sighs] Kira made an offer…

215
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:41,284
As long as the NPA agrees
not to pursue him anymore,

216
00:11:41,451 --> 00:11:43,953
he won't lay a hand on any politicians.

217
00:11:45,914 --> 00:11:48,499
So, that's that.
The police caved into him.

218
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,126
[all gasp]

219
00:11:50,752 --> 00:11:53,755
Mogi and I have already
made up our minds on this.

220
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:56,299
Aizawa, Matsuda…

221
00:11:56,507 --> 00:11:58,301
if you wish to continue working this case,

222
00:11:58,384 --> 00:12:01,346
you'll have to hand in
your letter of resignation to the NPA.

223
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,139
Just as Mogi and I are going to do.

224
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:04,307
[both gasp]

225
00:12:04,557 --> 00:12:08,519
Like it or not, you cannot pursue Kira
as member of the police force anymore.

226
00:12:08,603 --> 00:12:10,438
Wha… Hold-- Hold on a second, Chief.

227
00:12:10,980 --> 00:12:12,565
They made it quite clear.

228
00:12:12,857 --> 00:12:15,485
If you continue to work with L
you will be fired.

229
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:17,278
That's all there is to it.

230
00:12:17,403 --> 00:12:19,322
So then, Chief, you're gonna…

231
00:12:20,281 --> 00:12:23,076
In a few hours,
I'm no longer going to be your chief.

232
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:26,829
However, we all have our own lives.

233
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:28,873
So, think it over carefully.

234
00:12:29,249 --> 00:12:30,541
That's true, Chief.

235
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:33,044
Especially, if you've got family
to support.

236
00:12:33,127 --> 00:12:34,003
[breathes heavily]

237
00:12:35,505 --> 00:12:38,591
[Ryuzaki] If you want my opinion,
you'd be better off as police officers.

238
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:39,884
[Yagami] Hmm?

239
00:12:40,009 --> 00:12:42,595
[Ryuzaki] I was alone
when I started this case.

240
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:46,599
And although I'm grateful to all of you
for staying with me as long as you have,

241
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:49,435
I know that I can do this by myself.

242
00:12:49,811 --> 00:12:51,646
I'll be sure to visit you
at the department

243
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:55,358
and bring you Kira's head as a reward
for all that you've sacrificed.

244
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:56,901
Ryuzaki!

245
00:12:57,026 --> 00:12:59,612
As long as I'm alive,
you won't be working alone.

246
00:12:59,988 --> 00:13:01,781
-You have my word on that!
-[chain rattles]

247
00:13:02,699 --> 00:13:03,908
[Ryuzaki] Hm. That's right.

248
00:13:04,075 --> 00:13:06,577
I'll have Light working with me
until I catch Kira,

249
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:08,288
so I won't be alone after all.

250
00:13:08,705 --> 00:13:12,583
But as I said, I think the rest of you
should remain as police officers.

251
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,335
But when you first contacted us,

252
00:13:14,419 --> 00:13:17,213
you said that you'd need the help
of the police in order to solve this case.

253
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:19,924
[Ryuzaki] That's because the police
as an organization,

254
00:13:20,008 --> 00:13:22,176
were still hoping to arrest Kira.

255
00:13:22,302 --> 00:13:23,428
They weren't bowing to him.

256
00:13:23,553 --> 00:13:25,680
Besides, with all due respect,
there's a big difference

257
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:29,058
between the help of two or three civilians
and the police as an organization.

258
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:32,603
Mm. And as you said,
the police have made their position clear.

259
00:13:32,687 --> 00:13:35,523
They don't wanna catch Kira,
so let's just leave it at that. [swallows]

260
00:13:35,648 --> 00:13:36,649
[sighs]

261
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:39,152
Well, I suppose what you're saying
makes sense.

262
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:42,655
If we are not police officers anymore,
we won't be of much use to you.

263
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:45,575
However, we're all
personally involved in this.

264
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:48,286
All of us have risked our lives
to catch Kira.

265
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:51,122
Doesn't that give us the right to decide

266
00:13:51,247 --> 00:13:53,791
whether we stay here
or return to the police force?

267
00:13:54,167 --> 00:13:55,626
Hmm. Good point.

268
00:13:56,044 --> 00:13:58,504
Then by all means, please,
make your decision.

269
00:13:59,589 --> 00:14:02,759
But, Chief, wait. If you quit your job
with the police force,

270
00:14:02,884 --> 00:14:04,344
you'll be unemployed.

271
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:08,222
Even if we do catch Kira,
what are you gonna do after that?

272
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,600
-[Matsuda] Oh…
-After that?

273
00:14:11,059 --> 00:14:14,937
I hadn't really thought of it,
but I suppose after we catch Kira…

274
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:19,359
I'll have to dust off my resume.

275
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:21,319
Count me in!

276
00:14:21,486 --> 00:14:23,988
I'm gonna quit the police
and chase Kira too, Chief!

277
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,824
And I still have my job
as Misa-Misa's manager!

278
00:14:26,908 --> 00:14:28,951
Besides, if I stayed on
as a police officer,

279
00:14:29,035 --> 00:14:30,411
I'd feel like a total loser.

280
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,747
[Yagami] Think before you open
your mouth, Matsuda.

281
00:14:33,122 --> 00:14:34,290
Oh…

282
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:38,002
[Aizawa] Uh…

283
00:14:39,462 --> 00:14:40,380
Uh…

284
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:45,468
Is there any way I could still keep my job
and help you in my spare time?

285
00:14:45,635 --> 00:14:47,345
[sighs] There isn't.

286
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:50,139
If you remain a police officer,
then please, don't come back here.

287
00:14:51,516 --> 00:14:53,226
But you know I won't leak any information.

288
00:14:53,351 --> 00:14:55,603
I won't be sharing any of our information.

289
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:57,105
[gasps]

290
00:14:57,855 --> 00:15:00,775
You are free to pursue Kira on your own,
if you want to.

291
00:15:01,442 --> 00:15:03,277
But I don't think
it's fair to your families

292
00:15:03,361 --> 00:15:06,697
to burden them by giving up
your livelihood just to continue this…

293
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:08,908
I can't see how that's a good idea.

294
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:12,328
It's as Ryuzaki says,

295
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:14,831
no one here is gonna blame you
for quitting.

296
00:15:14,956 --> 00:15:15,998
Yeah. Right.

297
00:15:16,165 --> 00:15:18,334
We all understand why you gotta do this.

298
00:15:18,543 --> 00:15:20,920
But the Chief has a family, too.

299
00:15:21,712 --> 00:15:24,215
Our situations are completely different.

300
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,427
[sighs] Damn it.

301
00:15:27,677 --> 00:15:30,096
To leave now
after all we have been through…

302
00:15:30,388 --> 00:15:33,433
I said I was prepared to die
if that's what it took to catch him

303
00:15:33,516 --> 00:15:34,642
and I meant it.

304
00:15:35,309 --> 00:15:38,855
What kind of friend would I be to Ukita
if I quit now?

305
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:41,774
I became a detective,
so I could catch the bad guys,

306
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,151
not run away!

307
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:45,528
[Watari] Ryuzaki.

308
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:48,865
Early on in the investigation,
you specifically told me

309
00:15:48,990 --> 00:15:51,284
that if a task force member
were to lose their job,

310
00:15:51,367 --> 00:15:52,702
under any circumstances,

311
00:15:52,869 --> 00:15:54,495
I should make preparations to ensure

312
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:57,123
that their family's financial future
was secured.

313
00:15:57,206 --> 00:16:00,668
If you recall, a trust was set aside
for that very purpose.

314
00:16:01,335 --> 00:16:04,380
I'm a little curious as to why
you're withholding this information?

315
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:07,508
-[gasps]
-This is not the time or place, Watari.

316
00:16:08,176 --> 00:16:09,218
[Watari] I'm sorry.

317
00:16:09,469 --> 00:16:12,221
No way! So, all this time
we had nothing to worry about?

318
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,890
I can't believe you did that!

319
00:16:14,015 --> 00:16:16,100
There you go, Aizawa.
Isn't that a great news?

320
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:17,435
[gasps] Oh?

321
00:16:21,481 --> 00:16:24,609
Ryuzaki,
I assume that was some kind of test

322
00:16:24,692 --> 00:16:26,986
to determine how committed I was
to this task force.

323
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:29,071
It-- It-- It's not like that, Aizawa.

324
00:16:29,238 --> 00:16:31,491
Ryuzaki's just not the type
to say things directly.

325
00:16:31,574 --> 00:16:33,117
You should know that by now.

326
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:34,368
Yeah, that's right.

327
00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:35,995
-[Ryuzaki] No.
-[all] Huh?

328
00:16:37,413 --> 00:16:38,706
[Ryuzaki] I was testing you.

329
00:16:38,998 --> 00:16:41,083
I wanted to see
which one you would choose.

330
00:16:41,792 --> 00:16:43,419
-Oh.
-Ryuzaki…

331
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:47,215
[breathes forcefully]

332
00:16:47,924 --> 00:16:51,260
Fine then!
If I wasn't sure before, I am now!

333
00:16:51,511 --> 00:16:52,637
But Aizawa!

334
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:54,472
Let's face it.

335
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:56,933
I wasn't able to decide right away,
like you guys.

336
00:16:57,099 --> 00:16:59,560
I was leaning towards
going back to the police.

337
00:16:59,977 --> 00:17:01,854
Come on, Aizawa. Don't be so stubborn.

338
00:17:01,979 --> 00:17:03,147
[Aizawa] No! I quit!

339
00:17:03,481 --> 00:17:05,691
Now, I know this for sure!

340
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,902
I've always hated Ryuzaki!

341
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:10,488
I hate him and his way of doing things!

342
00:17:12,406 --> 00:17:14,951
[Ryuzaki] That's too bad,
because I like you, Aizawa.

343
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:16,953
[gasps]

344
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:18,829
[growls quietly]

345
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:21,958
I also hate the way
you've always gotta have the last word!

346
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:24,252
You insult me
and now you say something like that?

347
00:17:24,377 --> 00:17:25,920
That's it! I am outta here!

348
00:17:26,337 --> 00:17:27,463
Thank you for everything.

349
00:17:28,839 --> 00:17:30,758
[door opens]

350
00:17:32,218 --> 00:17:34,095
[door closes]

351
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:41,644
[Light] I just found another one.

352
00:17:41,936 --> 00:17:45,273
A general manager of a bank,
Yotsuba's biggest competitor,

353
00:17:45,356 --> 00:17:48,943
on September 7th, he slipped and fell
on the front steps of his house and died.

354
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:49,986
Instantly.

355
00:17:50,444 --> 00:17:53,030
[Yagami] September 7th was a Friday,
wasn't it?

356
00:17:53,281 --> 00:17:54,198
[Light and Ryuzaki] Hm?

357
00:17:54,282 --> 00:17:56,325
After going over this again,
I noticed something.

358
00:17:56,492 --> 00:17:58,619
All the deaths
which are beneficial to Yotsuba,

359
00:17:58,786 --> 00:18:00,496
are concentrated around the weekends.

360
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:02,790
Huh? On the weekends?

361
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,000
With the first few victims

362
00:18:04,125 --> 00:18:06,002
the time of death
appears to have been random,

363
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:10,423
More recently they all take place between
Friday night and Saturday afternoon.

364
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,842
I'm amazed
that you even noticed that, Chief.

365
00:18:13,050 --> 00:18:15,720
Matsuda, I thought I told you
to stop calling me "Chief."

366
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:18,514
I'm sorry,
but you'll always be the Chief to me.

367
00:18:19,015 --> 00:18:21,475
This is a really important clue, Dad.
Nice work.

368
00:18:21,851 --> 00:18:25,271
Well, you know, I can't let myself
fall behind you and Ryuzaki.

369
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:28,107
After all, the last thing I want
is to be dead weight.

370
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:30,151
Oh. "Dead weight"?

371
00:18:30,735 --> 00:18:32,570
[Ryuzaki] Is Kira someone from Yotsuba?

372
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,072
Or is Kira simply using Yotsuba?

373
00:18:35,156 --> 00:18:36,532
I haven't figured that out yet,

374
00:18:36,616 --> 00:18:40,036
but we will proceed under the assumption
that this is Kira's doing.

375
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:42,705
We will focus on Yotsuba.

376
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:46,626
[grunts] This is all
of the Yotsuba Group's employees.

377
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:47,918
Here.

378
00:18:48,169 --> 00:18:49,503
Thank you very much.

379
00:18:49,754 --> 00:18:51,631
[Light] That's 300,000 people.

380
00:18:51,714 --> 00:18:53,799
How did he put this together so quickly?

381
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,217
That's amazing, Mogi.

382
00:18:55,843 --> 00:18:58,179
[Ryuzaki] He's been incredibly efficient
from the start.

383
00:18:59,013 --> 00:19:00,056
Ryuzaki!

384
00:19:00,181 --> 00:19:03,059
Please, tell me, is there anything
I can do to help with the investigation?

385
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:04,352
Besides the manager thing.

386
00:19:05,269 --> 00:19:07,063
[Ryuzaki] So, you really wanna be useful?

387
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:08,272
Yes!

388
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:10,733
[Ryuzaki] Then could you get me
another cup of coffee?

389
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:12,026
Huh?

390
00:19:12,693 --> 00:19:14,445
[Ryuzaki] And for our guests
over there as well.

391
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:15,696
Huh?

392
00:19:17,198 --> 00:19:18,240
Who are they?

393
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:19,950
Hold on a sec. Who let them in?

394
00:19:20,868 --> 00:19:23,746
Those two are the newest members
of the task force.

395
00:19:27,083 --> 00:19:30,461
The name's Aiber.
I'm a conman. How's it going?

396
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:33,589
I'm Wedy. And I'm a thief by trade.

397
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:36,634
Oh. A conman and a thief?

398
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:40,304
That's right. Aiber is a lifelong conman.

399
00:19:40,471 --> 00:19:42,640
His unparalleled social skills

400
00:19:42,765 --> 00:19:45,226
allow him to befriend
and gain the trust of any target.

401
00:19:45,643 --> 00:19:47,103
We'll use him for infiltration.

402
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:48,604
As for Wedy,

403
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:52,024
she is a thief who specializes
in cracking high-end security systems.

404
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:53,150
As proof of that,

405
00:19:53,234 --> 00:19:56,445
she was able to enter the building
without setting off a single alarm.

406
00:19:57,571 --> 00:20:00,116
You expect us to work with criminals?

407
00:20:00,241 --> 00:20:01,325
Yes, that is correct.

408
00:20:01,409 --> 00:20:03,369
However, these two
have never once been caught.

409
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,538
So, it's unlikely
they'll be killed by Kira.

410
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:08,290
Think of them
as professionals of the underworld.

411
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,000
I understand.

412
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:11,377
To investigate Yotsuba,

413
00:20:11,460 --> 00:20:13,629
we're gonna need the help
of people like this.

414
00:20:14,755 --> 00:20:17,133
Let's all do our part
and make this happen, okay?

415
00:20:17,341 --> 00:20:19,468
-Yeah!
-Yeah. Deal.

416
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:31,772
[girl laughs]

417
00:20:33,399 --> 00:20:34,942
Oh? Daddy?

418
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:36,861
-Huh?
-[giggles] Daddy!

419
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:39,238
Oh, Yumi…

420
00:20:39,655 --> 00:20:40,781
Eriko…

421
00:20:41,031 --> 00:20:43,451
What are you doing here?
Shouldn't you be at work right now?

422
00:20:43,951 --> 00:20:46,454
You need to tell me
if you're planning to be home for dinner.

423
00:20:46,662 --> 00:20:49,165
I just went shopping
and I only bought for me and Yumi.

424
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:52,001
You can eat my dinner
and I'll have dessert instead!

425
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:53,252
Sorry.

426
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:56,380
It was sort of a last-minute decision,
but they just gave me some time off.

427
00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:59,550
Huh? Is a "time off" a vacation, Daddy?

428
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:01,260
Yeah. That's right.

429
00:21:01,552 --> 00:21:02,595
Yippee!

430
00:21:03,137 --> 00:21:05,848
From now on,
I can have a break every single week.

431
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:09,477
Now I can go with you to the park.

432
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:13,314
[trembling]
Maybe we can go to the zoo together,

433
00:21:13,731 --> 00:21:15,441
or the amusement park…

434
00:21:15,941 --> 00:21:17,902
[Aizawa sobbing]

435
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,529
Ooh. What's wrong, Dad?

436
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:25,326
[Yumi] Mommy, why is Daddy crying?

437
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:27,703
[Aizawa sobbing]

438
00:21:28,579 --> 00:21:33,626
TO BE CONTINUED
